### Step 3: Verify README structure

The README at `sdk/advisor/Azure.ResourceManager.Advisor/README.md` has all required sections but two need content improvements:

| Section | Status | Action needed |
|---------|--------|---------------|
| Getting started | ✅ Complete | No change |
| Key concepts | ⚠️ Stub (generic link only) | Add brief descriptions of each resource type (see Step 1) |
| Examples | ❌ No inline code | Add snippet placeholders pointing to the new sample files (see Step 1) |
| Troubleshooting | ✅ Complete | No change |
| Next steps | ✅ Complete | No change |
| Contributing | ✅ Complete | No change |

Use `sdk/keyvault/Azure.Security.KeyVault.Secrets/README.md` as the canonical reference for section formatting and tone.

### Step 4: Validate

Run these commands in order. Each must succeed before proceeding to the next:

1. `dotnet build sdk/advisor/Azure.ResourceManager.Advisor/`
2. `dotnet test sdk/advisor/Azure.ResourceManager.Advisor/ --filter TestCategory!=Live`
3. `eng/scripts/Update-Snippets.ps1 advisor` — reads `#region Snippet:` tags from test files and injects code into README placeholder blocks; check the git diff after running to confirm README was updated correctly
4. `eng/scripts/Export-API.ps1 advisor` — regenerates public API listing files; required since new public types were added
5. `dotnet format sdk/advisor/Azure.ResourceManager.Advisor/`

</details>

